{
  "stem": "10587.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 1.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it was a tranquil type of a community, even so that we always felt that the anti-Semitism was always present, from-- coming from the Poles, from non-Jew Poles.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And-- but we didn't have much trouble with it because they-- everyone of the city was-- knew the name Enoch because of-- we were-- since it was a very old, established name.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And also my grandfather had a hardware store in-- in center of town, which was right in the main centrum, in the main square.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] I used to horse around quite a bit with my younger brother, and we were always very happy and-- and disruptive, to the point where my mother named me Haman.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And every time I'm used to come back from school, or from cheder, she says-- she used to say, run for your life, Haman is coming.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Unfortunately, my younger brother was killed in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He never survived the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The 17-- my-- the Bader family, which actually in Poland it was pronounced 'Bah-der.' They-- they dated back to the 17th century in Wadowice My grandfather Jacob and Tamara Bader were my grandparents.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had quite a few uncles and aunts.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were like, I think, 10 children, many cousins and uncles.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "A big family.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I used to visit Wadowice quite often, especially during vacation time when school was out.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] at home, we were six children.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we were a very happy bunch.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We always [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] waited for the-- for Sabbath, for Shabbos, for the Saturday, because my mother used to bake quite a few cakes, various types of cakes like streuselkuchen, and moon cake, cheesecake, and maybe four or five different cakes.",
      "word_count": 43
    }
  ],
